==English==
===Etymology===
From the larger expression "It's the last straw that breaks the camel's back".
  
===Noun phrase===
'''[[last]] [[straw]]'''

#{{slang}} A small addition to a burden which causes it to exceed the capacity.  
#:''That's the '''last straw'''; it's a petty demand but I'm already under too much work.  I quit!''

